    <bodyContent>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>One branch of Dr Knowles' research is on the psychophysiology of stress responses. Her recent work in this area focuses on the extent to which adverse childhood experiences (ACEs) can affect the healthy functioning of this response via alterations in perception. She is also interested in wider social perception research in political psychology and political behaviour. She has recently published work examining the perception of leadership <a href="https://eresearch.qmu.ac.uk/handle/20.500.12289/9891" title="eResearch link to Dr Kirsten Knowles publications">during the 2014 Scottish independence referendum</a> and has contributed to an edited book on the <a href="https://eresearch.qmu.ac.uk/handle/20.500.12289/9925" title="rResearch publications - Kirsten Knowles">evolutionary psychology of leadership perception</a>.</p>]]></Value>
    </bodyContent>
